# Dashboard Patterns

- Use `width="stretch"` on charts and dataframes (NOT the deprecated `use_container_width`)
- All data loading wrapped in `@st.cache_data(ttl=300)` functions
- Imports from `src/` happen inside cache functions to avoid circular imports at module level
- Color palette: primary `#4F46E5`, accent `#7C3AED`, success `#10B981`, danger `#EF4444`, warning `#F59E0B`
- Risk tier colors: High → `#EF4444`, Medium → `#F59E0B`, Low → `#10B981`
- Use `st.metric()` via the `metric_card()` helper for KPI display
- Charts use Plotly (`px` for quick plots, `go` for complex ones)
- Page structure: title → KPI row → charts in columns → detail tables
